result.execSummary:
The defendant Kelsey L Breedlove was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Pay $3200.00 stipulated restitution to Brent K. Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, the Court ordered monies taken from up to 25% of prison funds; balance to be paid while on extended supervision. Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Pay the DNA surcharge, all costs and disbursements after restitution has been paid. Should defendant get revoked, Court ordered that monies be taken from prison funds not to exceed 25%. Balance to be paid while on extended supervision. Failure to pay would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant, which is non-dischargable in bankruptcy.

Seek and maintain employment.
Job and vocational training.

No contact with Brent K., or his family or their residence.
